<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.5151/278: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-16T19:00:00-04:00">September 16, 1937—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>389. Your 763, September 1, 6 p.m. You may take up the matter informally
                            with the Ministry of State with a view to ascertaining whether it would
                            not be possible for the Exchange Control Board to revert to the policy
                            previously followed of permitting American citizens so desiring to
                            return checks on foreign banks, especially in view of the small amounts
                            probably involved.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
